  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The research study proposed is designed to examine the outcomes of a cognitive behavioral
      guided self-care intervention with older adults diagnosed with generalized anxiety disorder
      and recruited from a primary care setting. It is hypothesized that the cognitive behavioral
      guided self-care intervention will produce greater declines in worry and anxiety than
      enhanced usual care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
